description.narrative: A strategic framework for out-of-school children, based on equity and inclusion, developed, adopted and key interventions implemented, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Communication And Advocacy, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews, Equity â€“ Focus On Girls' And Inclusive Education, Evaluation, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: A regulatory framework that increases access to quality early learning and establishes standards of quality interverventions in primary schools, according to the CFS framework, in place and interventions implemented

description.narrative: The COVID emergency response stimulated UNICEF and the Ministry of Education (MoE) to facilitate the rapid development of new approaches to broaden the range of platforms to provide children with routine learning at home in a safe environment and promote their return to school. Partnership with the Ministry of Communication (MoC), the national television network, community radios and civil society organizations provided child-friendly distance education through TV, radio, and online learning, for more than 300,000 children. The tripartite memorandum of understanding between MoE, National Television and UNICEF is a major achievement that has reduced the production costs of TV-lessons. | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/01/2022
